text: todays mailbag
i dont know hot oo respond, ive never had someone be argumentative with me lol
I'm mostly just surprised you haven't had someone be argumentative before
I can see why he would want to see Ishai with only cards of her color identity
Sure but that’s a feature request vs exposing a core philosophical goal of the site.

>>>
Thanks for the thought Brian. I just looked into it and there really isn’t enough data to produce good pages and justify spending time on making a special page for this over other stuff. For example, I have 19 decks for Ishtai, a commander that has been out for 2 years. Even that data there is fairly stale. I have to play into “selection bias” because if the data isn’t there there is not much I can do and it’s hard for me to justify spending time on a special case that will yield questionable results.

You should never feel that my website is telling you what to do or if you are doing something incorrect or correct. It’s just a tool to get some ideas and optimize decks. Commander is fun because you can do what you want and still be relevant in most games.

To help you with your Ishai project, have you heard of advanced filters? What I did in the link below is filtered out a bunch of the popular cards that are outside of the u/w color identity. After all this filtering t’s mostly u/w.  I went a bit overboard, you could have stopped after 3-4 cards and had mostly u/w cards in the list.

-Don

<https://edhrec.com/commanders/ishai-ojutai-dragonspeaker?f=out%3DCorpsejack+Menace%3Bout%3DIzzet+Signet%3Bout%3DEternal+Witness%3Bout%3DSimic+Signet%3Bout%3DTaurean+Mauler%3Bout%3DBirds+of+Paradise%3Bout%3DBaleful+Strix%3Bout%3DCultivate%3Bout%3DMystic+Monastery%3Bout%3DKruphix%2C+God+of+Horizons%3Bout%3DMerciless+Eviction%3Bout%3DDemonic+Tutor>

So do we control the ranking for Scryfall's EDHREC sort?
Yea
What up?
I'm just curious how the rank works. Looking at Uncommon Legendary Creatures from Dominaria, Hallar is ranked last while Rona and Adeliz are higher. Hallar is in like 60 decks while Rona is just in 6
Are they all tied because they're new and that's just how it happened to sort? Or am I missing some detail?
I think it’s based upon inclusion IN decks. Not how many decks they lead. Hallar is in 6 decks to Rona’s 26 and Adeliz’s 36
Interesting... Shouldn't the "in deck" number be (N of decks leading + N of decks in 99) ?
It is the number in decks
I could add them. Thats an interesting idea
I can see why for non-legendary cards
Since I can't lead my deck with an artifact or enchantment
So adding them would, I guess, give Legendary Creatures a boost over everything else
